Here's how you can update your three buttons (Add, Delete Selected, Refresh) to use normal icons that closely match the FIS Data Integrity Manager UI â€” using Font Awesome (recommended for full styling control and modern icon set):


---

âœ… Step 1: Add Font Awesome to your index.html

In src/index.html, add this inside the <head>:

<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.0/css/all.min.css">


---

âœ… Step 2: Updated Button HTML Code

Replace your existing buttons with the following HTML:

<div class="button-group">
  <p-button class="custom-btn">
    <ng-template pTemplate="content">
      <i class="fas fa-plus"></i> Add
    </ng-template>
  </p-button>

  <p-button class="custom-btn danger" (click)="deleteSelectedRates()">
    <ng-template pTemplate="content">
      <i class="fas fa-trash-alt"></i> Delete Selected
    </ng-template>
  </p-button>

  <p-button class="custom-btn" (click)="refreshPage()">
    <ng-template pTemplate="content">
      <i class="fas fa-sync-alt"></i> Refresh
    </ng-template>
  </p-button>
</div>


---

âœ… Step 3: CSS Styling for FIS Look

Add this to your componentâ€™s .css file:

.button-group {
  display: flex;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.custom-btn {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  border: 1px solid #d0d0d0;
  color: #333;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 4px 12px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

.custom-btn i {
  margin-right: 5px;
}

.custom-btn:hover {
  background-color: #e0e0e0;
  border-color: #bcbcbc;
}

.custom-btn.danger {
  background-color: #fdd;
  border-color: #f99;
  color: #b00;
}

.custom-btn.danger:hover {
  background-color: #fbb;
  border-color: #f55;
}


